CountVectorizer was utilized to transform the messages by counting the occurrences of each character present in each message. The feature extraction parameters 'char_wb' and ngrams(1,1) were employed. 'char_wb' is a particular type of feature representation in which the text is divided into "n-grams" ofcharacters. The ngram_range parameter specifies the range of character n-grams that should be used in the vectorization process; in this case,CountVectorizer considers only 1-grams, also known as unigrams. To convert the text data into a numeric representation that can be easily processed bymachine learning algorithms, Vectorizer.fit_transform was used.

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

data = [[93, 93, 93],
        [95, 95, 95],
        [93, 93, 93],
        [94, 94, 94]]

classifiers = ['Logistic Regression', 'Random Forest', 'MLPClassifier', 'Hybrid Classifier']
metrics = ['Precision', 'Accuracy', 'Recall']

X = np.arange(len(classifiers))
bar_width = 0.2

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 4))

for i, metric in enumerate(metrics):
    plt.bar(X + (i * bar_width), [row[i] for row in data], width=bar_width, label=metric)

plt.xlabel('Classifiers')
plt.ylabel('Scores')
plt.title('Comparison of Classifier Metrics')
plt.xticks(X + bar_width, classifiers)
plt.legend()

plt.show()
